<br>
<strong>REFERENCE LIST ENTRY</strong>
<br>
<br>
Add a reference list at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	Authors. (Year of publication). Title of article. <em>Name of Journal, volume</em>(issue), 
	page numbers. DOI (if assigned)
</blockquote>
<br>
For works without a DOI, if the work was accessed from a website (excluding online academic 
research databases, e.g., ProQuest, EBSCO and ScienceDirect) include the URL in the reference. 
Works accessed from an academic database do not require a URL or detail about the database in 
the reference list. In this case, the work would be referenced in the same manner as a print 
version of the work.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	<span class="hover" title="Authors">Smith, A., &amp; Brown, B.</span> 
	(<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">2017</span>). 
	<span class="hover" title="Title of article">A battle from the beginning: The life and times of a heavyweight champion</span>. 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Name of Journal">Sport and Fitness</span>, 
	<span class="hover" title="volume">14</span></em>(<span class="hover" title="issue">2</span>), 
	<span class="hover" title="page numbers">25&#45;37</span>. 
	<span class="hover fake-aref" title="DOI">https://doi.org/10.12:3456789012</span>
</blockquote>
<br>
URLs and DOIs are displayed as a hyperlink.
<br>
<br>
If the source displays the DOI number only (e.g., 10.1036/0071393756), convert the DOI into a link 
by adding <span class="fake-aref">https://doi.org/</span> before the number.
<br>
